          "lecture_id": "statistics_estimation_001",
          "span": "Maximum likelihood estimation uses the log-likelihood as its objective and selects a parameter value that maximizes it:\n\n\\[\n\\widehat{\\theta}_{\\mathrm{MLE}} = \\operatorname*{arg\\,max}_{\\theta}\\, \\ell(\\theta).\n\\]"
        },
        {
          "lecture_id": "statistics_estimation_001",
          "span": "The log-likelihood is obtained by taking the logarithm of the likelihood. Independence turns the product into a sum:\n\n\\[\n\\ell(\\theta) = \\log L(\\theta; x_{1:n}) = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} \\log p(x_i \\mid \\theta).\n\\]"
        }
      ],
      "rationale": "The Maximum Likelihood Estimator Formula formalizes the Likelihood Formula by defining the estimator as the argmax of the log-likelihood, which is derived from the likelihood."
    }
  ]
